C%22%3Elack%20of%20compelling%20things%20to%20buy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Buffett%20is%20a%20value%20investor%20who%20specializes%20in%20sniffing%20out%20bargains%2C%20and%20those%20have%20become%20rare%20finds%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20heard%20every%20speculative%20idea%20imaginable%2C%20from%20accumulating%20capital%20for%20a%20doomsday%20scenario%20to%20planning%20to%20make%20a%20gigantic%20cash%20dividend%2C%26quot%3B%20Lawrence%20Cunningham%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Delaware's%20Weinberg%20Center%20on%20Corporate%20Governance%20and%20the%20author%20of%20several%20books%20about%20Buffett%20and%20Berkshire%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20rationale%20for%20Berkshire's%20cash%20pile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20seem%20far-fetched%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20likely%20cause%20of%20cash%20buildup%20at%20Berkshire%20is%20absence%20of%20attractive%20capital%20deployment%20opportunities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECunningham%20said%20stocks%20have%20surged%20to%20record%20highs%2C%20private-business%20valuations%20have%20jumped%2C%20Berkshire-owned%20businesses%20like%20Geico%20and%20See's%20Candies%20can%20only%20deploy%20so%20much%20money%2C%20and%20Berkshire's%20Class%20A%20shares%20have%20climbed%20to%20record%20levels%20of%20about%20%24700%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3b860b8-e36d-438f-8b07-098f7d688267%5C%22%3EHot%20stocks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20stock%20market's%20total%20value%20hit%20a%20record%20high%20of%20%2458.13%20trillion%20on%20Monday%2C%20an%20unprecedented%20198.1%25%20of%20US%20GDP%20last%20quarter%2C%20Wilshire%20Indexes%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20metric%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-indicator-stock-market-outlook-bubble-crash-ai-tech-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuffett%20Indicator%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20investor%20once%20hailed%20it%20as%20an%20excellent%20yardstick%20for%20valuations.%20Buffett%20said%20it%20should%20have%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20strong%20warning%20signal%26quot%3B%20when%20the%20measure%20spiked%20during%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%2C%20and%20buying%20stocks%20when%20it%20nears%20200%25%20is%20%26quot%3Bplaying%20with%20fire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wilshire%205000's%20elevated%20level%20makes%20%26quot%3Bthis%20stock%20market%20the%20most%20overvalued%20in%20history%20%E2%80%94%20even%20higher%20than%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20tech%20bubble%20in%202001-2002%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20Dietrich%2C%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20at%20B.%20Riley%20Wealth%20Management%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20little%20surprise%2C%20then%2C%20that%20Buffett%20didn't%20buy%20back%20a%20single%20Berkshire%20share%20last%20quarter%20after%20spending%20%2420%20billion%20on%20repurchases%20between%20the%20start%20of%202022%20and%20June%2030%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20likely%20because%20he%20and%20his%20team%20no%20longer%20see%20their%20company's%20stock%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-stock-buybacks-reasons-loves-face-bailout-ban-coronavirus-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20value%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20team%20has%20also%20been%20paring%20Berkshire's%20stock%20portfolio.%20They%20sold%20%24133%20billion%20of%20stock%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sum%20that%20exceeds%20Citigroup's%20market%20cap%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20and%20bought%20less%20than%20%246%20billion%20worth%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20cut%20Apple%2C%20their%20most%20valuable%20holding%2C%20by%2060%25%20in%20that%20timeframe.%20They%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-bank-of-america-stock-sales-apple-portfolio-berkshire-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrimmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20B