0this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20policy%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20started%20lowering%20rates%2C%20but%20mortgage%20rates%20remain%20elevated%20thanks%20to%20uncertainty%20around%20how%20inflation%20will%20trend%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20and%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Mortgage%20Rate%20Projection%20for%202024%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Rate%20Projection%20for%202024%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202025%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20drop%20much%20further%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20started%20ticking%20up%20from%20historic%20lows%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202021%20and%20increased%20dramatically%20in%202022%20and%20throughout%20most%20of%202023.%20But%20now%20that%20inflation%20has%20decelerated%20and%20the%20Fed%20is%20expected%20to%20cut%20rates%20soon%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20trended%20down.%20In%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-september-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%20rose%20by%202.4%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20significant%20slowdown%20compared%20to%20when%20it%20peaked%20at%209.1%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20rates%20go%20down%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves.%20If%20economic%20conditions%20remain%20stable%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20not%20fall%20as%20much.%20But%20if%20the%20labor%20market%20weakens%20and%20the%20Fed%20has%20to%20cut%20rates%20more%20aggressively%2C%20we%20could%20see%20rates%20drop%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year