20point%20since%202009%2C%20when%20the%20market%20was%20reeling%20from%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis.%20Despite%20the%20hefty%20ready-to-sell%20supply%2C%20a%20sizable%20chunk%20of%20those%20homes%20may%20never%20be%20sold%20to%20regular%20buyers.%20That%20strange%20reality%20says%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20hurdles%20for%20would-be%20homeowners%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20builders%20and%20buyers%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20tricky%20position.%20Prices%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhome-prices-drop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinued%20their%20climb%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20most%20of%20the%20country.%20Mortgage%20rates%20dropped%20steadily%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20but%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-does-fed-impact-mortgage-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20head%20fake%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20span%20of%20a%20month%2C%20the%20typical%20rate%20for%20a%2030-year%20loan%20increased%20by%20almost%20a%20full%20percentage%20point%2C%20and%20could%20rise%20further.%20Throwing%20down%20for%20a%20starter%20home%20is%20about%2045%25%20more%20expensive%20than%20renting%2C%20a%20far%20wider%20gap%20than%20the%20historical%20average%20of%20about%2015%25%2C%20according%20to%20monthly%20expense%20data%20tracked%20by%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting.%20Builders%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20are%20luring%20buyers%20with%20some%20perks%20but%20are%20barely%20budging%20on%20prices.%20That's%20partly%20because%20these%20companies%20have%20another%20place%20to%20turn%3A%20the%20rental%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20strong%20demand%20for%20rentals%20and%20a%20tough%20sales%20market%2C%20some%20builders%20are%20choosing%20to%20convert%20for-sale%20homes%20into%20rentals%20or%20offload%20inventory%20to%20investors%20who%20specialize%20in%20single-family-home%20rentals.%20Opportunistic%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20small%20and%20midsize%20players%2C%20who%20own%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20single-family%20rentals%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20are%20happy%20to%20oblige.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20walls%20and%20a%20backyard%20are%20still%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%20For%20those%20who%20can't%20afford%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20(or%20don't%20want%20to%20right%20now)%2C%20the%20only%20option%20is%20to%20rent.%20That%20simple%20fact%20gives%20builders%20some%20breathing%20room%2C%20but%20it%20also%20means%20that%20a%20glut%20of%20new%20homes%20may%20not%20deliver%20the%20price%20cuts%20buyers%20have%20been%20anxiously%20awaiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-forecast-mortgage-rates-homebuilding-inventory-prices-2024-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egolden%20run%20for%20homebuilders%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20drawing%20to%20a%20close.%20When%20rising%20mortgage%20rates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-mortgage-rates-outlook-home-prices-affordability-wealth-gap-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrapped%20many%20would-be%20sellers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20homes%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20builders%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20big%20winners%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20wanted%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-construction-building-boom-last-hope-new-homebuyers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20bet%20was%20probably%20new%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20economist%20told%20me%20last%20year%20that%20builders%20were%20%26quot%3Bthe%20only%20game%20in%20town%26quot%3B%20in%20some%20areas.%20Builders%20not%20only%20offered%20a%20welcome%20alternative%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrozen%20resale%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20could%20cut%20deals%20to%20make%20their%20homes%20even%20more%20appealing%20to%20the%20average%20buyer%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuilders-turn-to-mortgage-rate-buydowns-as-affordability-sours-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMortgage-rate%20buydowns%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20builder%20pays%20the%20lender%20up%20front%20in%20exchange%20for%20lowering%20the%20buyer's%20loan%20rate%2C%20can%20save%20a%20new%20homeowner%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20even%20with%20the%20freebies%2C%20builders%20are%20selling%20homes%20at%20a%20slower-than-expected%20pace%20as%20buyers%20grapple%20with%20worsening%20affordability%2C%20sharp%20swings%20in%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20and%20general%20uncertainty%20%E2%80%94%20people%20would%20rather%20sit%20on%20the%20fence%20than%20leap%20into%20a%20market%20with%20so%20many%20unknowns.%20With%20slower%20sales%20across%20the%20board%2C%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20market%20has%20climbed.%20There%20were%20108%2C000%20finished%20homes%20for%20sale%20at%20the%20end%20of%20September%2C%20some%2048%25%20more%20than%20at%20the%20same%20point%20a%20year%20ago.%20There%20were%20258%2C000%20homes%20under%20construction%20but%20not%20yet%20sold%2C%20another%20sizable%20figure%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20same%20point%20in%202019%2C%20there%20were%20about%20194%2C000.%20Builders%20surveyed%20by%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%20said%20they%20had%20an%20average%20of%20about%202.5%20unsold%20homes%20in%20each%20of%20their%20communities%20in%20October%2C%20representing%20a%2047%25%20increase%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20In%20October%202021%2C%20they%20reported%20only%200.4%20unsold%20homes%20per%20community.%20Some%20of%20this%20increase%20is%20by%20design.%20Companies%20are%20building%20more%20homes%20%26quot%3Bon%20spec%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20before%20they%20have%20a%20buyer%2C%20to%20shorten%20timelines%20and%20compete%20directly%20with%20the%20resale%20market.%20But%20there's%20no%20question%20that%20builders%20have%20hit%20a%20snag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20might%20seem%20obvious%3A%20Cut%20prices!%20But%20builders%20will%20%26quot%3Btry%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20things%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Keith%20Hughes%2C%20an%20executive%20at%20the%20housing%20research%20firm%20Zonda.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20not%20seeing%20drastic%20price%20drops%20virtually%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%20Buyers%20may%20not%20be%20flooding%20the%20market%2C%20but%20there%20are%20fewer%20homes%20out%20there%2C%20too.%20The%20number%20of%20available%20homes%20for%20sale%20at%20the%20end%20of%20October%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRealtor.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealtor.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20about%2021%25%20lower%20than%20in%20the%20same%20month%20in%202019.%20Builders%20looking%20to%20move%20their%20product%20lean%20heavily%20on%20incentives%20%E2%80%94%20Lennar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20homebuilders%20in%20the%20country%2C%20said%20that%20the%20average%20sales%20incentives%20per%20home%20amounted%20to%20%2448%2C100%20from%20June%20through%20August%2C%20compared%20with%20%2436%2C400%20a%20year%20earlier.%20Builders%20are%20also%20completing%20smaller%20floor%20plans%20to%20match%20the%20needs%20of%20cost-conscious%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilders%20have%20another%20fallback%3A%20the%20rental%20market.%20Over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20homebuilders%20have%20forged%20relationships%20with%20companies%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-family-rental-investor-conference-buying-more-homes-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurchase%20thousands%20of%20single-family%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20manage%20them%20as%20rentals%20%E2%80%94%20if%20a%20builder%20were%20looking%20to%20move%20a%20portfolio%20of%20homes%2C%20they%20might%20find%20a%20willing%20buyer%20in%20a%20company%20like%20Pretium%2C%20which%20owns%20nearly%20100%2C000%20homes%2C%20or%20Invitation%20Homes%2C%20which%20manages%20a%20portfolio%20of%20more%20than%2085%2C000%20homes.%20Builders%20have%20also%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-single-family-rental-build-to-rent-houses-finance-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeveloping%20entire%20communities%20of%20single-family%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20rented%20out%20rather%20than%20sold%2C%20a%20strategy%20known%20as%20build-for-rent.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20meet%20the%20demand%20of%20renters%20who%20want%20their%20piece%20of%20the%20American%20dream%20%E2%80%94%20a%20home%20with%20a%20yard%20in%20a%20safe%20neighborhood%20with%20good%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20but%20either%20can't%20make%20a%20purchase%20or%20don't%20want%20to.%20Builders%20can%20sell%20to%20a%20guaranteed%20buyer%20willing%20to%20purchase%20in%20bulk%20or%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20homes%20and%20enjoy%20the%20steady%20returns%20of%20rental%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20advantages%2C%20the%20build-to-rent%20pipeline%20has%20become%20robust.%20D.R.%20Horton%2C%20the%20nation's%20biggest%20homebuilder%2C%20recently%20said%20it%20had%20about%20%24800%20million%20worth%20of%20single-family-rental%20property%20on%20its%20balance%20sheet%2C%20consisting%20of%203%2C140%20homes%20and%20about%201%2C900%20lots%20on%20which%20it%20can%20build%20more.%20Invitation%20Homes%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20owners%20of%20single-family%20rentals%2C%20recently%20said%20it%20expected%20to%20purchase%20nearly%202%2C500%20homes%20in%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20years%20from%20builders%20in%20places%20like%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%3B%20the%20Carolinas%3B%20and%20Houston.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOwners%20of%20single-family%20rentals%20have%20been%20around%20forever%2C%20but%20large%2C%20sophisticated%20SFR%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-family-rental-companies-institutional-backers-homes-wall-street-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrived%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis%20in%202008%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20investors%20began%20raising%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20pick%20up%20homes%20on%20the%20cheap.%20Now%20these%20companies%20represent%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20category%20of%20buyers%20that%20would%20really%20help%20a%20builder%20during%20a%20downturn%20unload%20some%20inventory%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Burns%2C%20of%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20podcast%20with%20Don%20Mullen%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Pretium.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20you're%20playing%20that%20out%20right%20now%2C%20you're%20already%20doing%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20big%20companies%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-americans-beating-wall-street-new-homes-real-estate-homebuying-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eown%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20all%20single-family%20rental%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they've%20been%20much%20more%20selective%20with%20their%20purchases%20as%20higher%20interest%20rates%20have%20made%20it%20tougher%20to%20get%20strong%20returns%20on%20their%20investments.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-and-pop-landlords-homeownership-rent-wall-street-corporate-investors-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20active%20buyers%20right%20now%20are%20small%20and%20midsize%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20own%20anywhere%20from%20a%20handful%20of%20homes%20to%20several%20hundred.%20With%20builders%20sitting%20on%20more%20homes%2C%20these%20investors%20are%20sniffing%20around%20for%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20investors%20are%20more%20or%20less%20saying%20to%20themselves%2C%20we're%20providing%20a%20solution%20here%20for%20builders%2C%20and%20that%20solution%20is%20inventory%20management%20and%20getting%20out%20of%20inventory%20that%20otherwise%20they're%20having%20trouble%20selling%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Adam%20Stern%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Strata%20SFR%2C%20a%20real-estate%20brokerage%20focused%20on%20single-family%20rentals%20and%20build-to-rent%20homes.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20that%20exit%20option.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forecasa.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForecasa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20real-estate%20analytics%20firm%2C%20indicates%20investors%20purchased%203%25%20to%205%25%20of%20homes%20sold%20by%20builders%20in%20the%20past%20three%20months.%20That%20may%20not%20sound%20like%20much%2C%20but%20a%20year%20ago%20that%20number%20was%20closer%20to%201%25.%20Some%20builders%20have%20recently%20been%20shuttling%20about%2010%25%20of%20their%20inventory%20to%20investors.%20Even%20then%2C%20these%20numbers%20may%20be%20undercounts%2C%20since%20some%20amateur%20rental%20owners%20may%20not%20be%20buying%20through%20the%20kinds%20of%20legal%20entities%20that%20tip%20off%20analysts%20to%20investor%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20small%20percentage%2C%20but%20if%20you%20think%20about%20just%20the%20sheer%20volume%20of%20properties%20that%20are%20being%20moved%2C%20it's%20a%20fairly%20large%20number%2C%20especially%20because%20it's%20growing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sean%20Morgan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Forecasa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20have%20mostly%20focused%20on%20Sun%20Belt%20markets%20like%20Nashville%20and%20Dallas%20in%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20US%2C%20where%20new%20construction%20is%20most%20plentiful.%20Builders%20may%20offer%20a%20slight%20discount%2C%20but%20they%20get%20something%20valuable%20in%20return%3A%20homes%20off%20their%20balance%20sheets.%20Builders%20often%20take%20on%20loans%20of%2012%20to%2024%20months%20to%20construct%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20before%20time%20is%20up%2C%20they%20have%20to%20either%20find%20a%20buyer%20or%20get%20a%20new%20loan.%20Local%20and%20regional%20builders%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20feel%20the%20squeeze%20than%20a%20national%20company%20like%20D.R.%20Horton%2C%20which%20can%20afford%20to%20keep%20homes%20on%20its%20books%20longer.%20When%20builders%20are%20staring%20down%20that%20ticking%20clock%2C%20%26quot%3Binvestors%20are%20natural%20buyers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Alex%20Offutt%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Business%20Purpose%20Capital%2C%20a%20capital%20provider%20for%20long-term%20investor%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilders%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20sell%2C%20though.%20Another%20route%20is%20to%20get%20a%20new%20long-term%20loan%20based%20on%20the%20rental%20income%20the%20properties%20will%20generate%2C%20then%20find%20tenants%20for%20the%20homes%20and%20wait%20to%20sell%20when%20the%20market%20is%20more%20favorable.%20Both%20Offutt%20and%20Ray%20Sturm%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20of%20Tower1%2C%20which%20offers%20financing%20for%20residential%20lenders%2C%20tell%20me%20they've%20been%20having%20more%20conversations%20with%20builders%20and%20their%20lenders%20who%20are%20seeking%20out%20this%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20know%20if%20they%20work%20on%20a%20rental%20campaign%2C%20they've%20got%20an%20exit%2C%26quot%3B%20Sturm%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20early%2C%20but%20it's%20bigger%20than%20I%20thought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20ideal%20scenario%20for%20most%20builders%2C%20especially%20since%20many%20aren't%20well%20versed%20in%20the%20minutiae%20of%20managing%20rental%20properties.%20But%20it%20could%20become%20another%20valuable%20off-ramp%20if%20they%20have%20trouble%20unloading%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20homebuilders%20are%20a%20long%20way%20from%20hitting%20the%20panic%20button.%20There's%20still%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-affordability-home-shortage-market-construction-population-cities-zillow-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20housing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20if%20there's%20a%20short-term%20oversupply%20in%20some%20places%2C%20and%20builders%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-homebuyers-mortgage-rates-spring-real-estate-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooking%20ahead%20to%20the%20spring%20buying%20season%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20true%20tell%20of%20where%20things%20are%20headed.%20Their%20embrace%20of%20the%20rental%20market%20says%20more%20about%20the%20obstacles%20for%20buyers%20than%20for%20builders.%20Prices%20and%20borrowing%20rates%20haven't%20provided%20relief%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20make%20a%20purchase.%20People%20who%20already%20own%20homes%20are%20reluctant%20to%20sell%20and%20move%20up%2C%20which%20means%20they're%20not%20freeing%20up%20the%20starter%20homes%20that%20first-time%20buyers%20crave.%20Would-be%20buyers%20have%20nowhere%20else%20to%20turn%20but%20the%20rental%20market%20%E2%80%94%20Redfin%20estimates%20that%20the%20number%20of%20renter%20households%20is%20growing%20three%20times%20as%20fast%20as%20homeowner%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20housing%20market%20%26quot%3Bis%20in%20limbo%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Selma%20Hepp%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20the%20real-estate%20data%20firm%20CoreLogic.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20sitting%20on%20the%20sidelines.%20It's%20waiting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuilders-new-construction-rental-homes-investors-price-cuts-mortgage-rates-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731492182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6733b760192f525898