ght%20on%20in%20several%20states%2C%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20'bulldozer%20justice'.%20State%20authorities%20have%2C%20in%20the%20past%2C%20said%20only%20illegal%20structures%20were%20demolished%20in%20such%20cases.%20But%20several%20petitions%20were%20filed%20before%20the%20court%2C%20flagging%20the%20extrajudicial%20nature%20of%20the%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20said%20it%20is%20the%20dream%20of%20every%20family%20to%20have%20a%20house%20and%20an%20important%20question%20before%20the%20court%20was%20whether%20the%20Executive%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20take%20away%20someone's%20shelter.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20dream%20of%20every%20person%2C%20every%20family%20to%20have%20a%20shelter%20above%20their%20heads.%20A%20house%20is%20an%20embodiment%20of%20the%20collective%20hopes%20of%20a%20family%20or%20individuals'%20stability%20and%20security.%C2%A0An%20important%20question%20as%20to%20whether%20the%20executive%20should%20be%20permitted%20to%20take%20away%20the%20shelter%20of%20a%20family%20or%20families%20as%20a%20measure%20for%20infliction%20of%20penalty%20on%20a%20person%20who%20is%20accused%20in%20a%20crime%20under%20our%20constitutional%20scheme%20or%20not%20arises%20for%20consideration%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0the%20judgment%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20considering%20the%20said%20question%2C%20we%20will%20be%20required%20to%20consider%20the%20principle%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20which%20is%20the%20very%20foundation%20of%20democratic%20governance.%20We%20will%20also%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution%20that%20provide%20protection%20to%20individuals%20from%20arbitrary%20state%20action.%20We%20will%20also%20have%20to%20consider%20in%20this%20case%20the%20issue%20with%20regard%20to%20fairness%20in%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20which%20mandates%20that%20the%20legal%20process%20should%20not%20prejudge%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused.%20We%20will%20also%20have%20to%20touch%20upon%20the%20concept%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20and%20the%20doctrine%20of%20public%20trust%20in%20respect%20of%20government%20officials%20holding%20their%20offices%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20adjudicatory%20functions%20are%20entrusted%20to%20the%20judiciary%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BExecutive%20cannot%20replace%20the%20Judiciary%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20executive%20in%20an%20arbitrary%20manner%20demolishes%20the%20houses%20of%20citizens%20only%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20they%20are%20accused%20of%20a%20crime%2C%20then%20it%20acts%20contrary%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%98rule%20of%20law'.%20If%20the%20executive%20acts%20as%20a%20judge%20and%20inflicts%20penalty%20of%20demolition%20on%20a%20citizen%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20he%20is%20an%20accused%2C%20it%20violates%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%98separation%20of%20powers'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20accountability%20must%20be%20fixed%20on%20public%20officials%20who%20take%20law%20into%20their%20hands%20and%20act%20in%20a%20high-handed%20manner.%20%26quot%3BState%20and%20its%20officials%20can't%20take%20arbitrary%20and%20excessive%20measures.%20If%20any%20officer%20of%20the%20State%20has%20abused%20his%20power%20or%20acted%20in%20total%20arbitrary%20or%20malafide%20manner%2C%20he%20cannot%20be%20spared%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20pointed%20that%20when%20a%20particular%20structure%20is%20chosen%20for%20demolition%20suddenly%20and%20similar%20other%20properties%20are%20not%20touched%2C%20then%20the%20presumption%20could%20be%20that%20the%20real%20motive%20was%20not%20razing%20the%20illegal%20structure%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bpenalising%20without%20trial%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20an%20average%20citizen%2C%20construction%20of%20a%20house%20is%20the%20culmination%20of%20years%20of%20hard%20work%2C%20dreams%20and%20aspirations.%20House%20embodies%20collective%20hope%20of%20security%20and%20future.%20If%20this%20is%20taken%20away%2C%20authorities%20must%20satisfy%20it%20is%20the%20only%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20questioned%20if%20authorities%20can%20demolish%20a%20house%20and%20deprive%20its%20residents%20of%20shelter%20if%20only%20one%20person%20residing%20there%20is%20an%20accused.%20%26quot%3BPunishing%20such%20persons%20who%20have%20no%20connection%20with%20the%20crime%20by%20demolishing%20the%20house%20where%20they%20live%20in%20or%20properties%20owned%20by%20them%20is%20nothing%20but%20an%20anarchy%20and%20would%20amount%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%C2%A0underlined%20that%20an%20individual%2C%20whether%20an%20accused%20or%20an%20undertrial%20or%20a%C2%A0%20a%20convict%2C%20have%20rights%20as%20any%20other%20citizen.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20right%20to%20dignity%20and%20cannot%20be%20subjected%20to%20any%20cruel%20or%20inhuman%20treatment.%20The%20punishment%20awarded%20to%20such%20persons%20has%20to%20be%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%20Such%20punishment%20cannot%20be%20inhuman%20or%20cruel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20accused%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20cannot%20be%20declared%20guilty%20%26quot%3Bunless%20proven%20so%20beyond%20reasonable%20doubt%20before%20a%20court%20of%20law%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThey%20cannot%20be%20declared%20guilty%2C%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20fair%20trial%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20chilling%20sight%20of%20a%20bulldozer%20demolishing%20a%20building%2C%20when%20authorities%20have%20failed%20to%20follow%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice%20and%20have%20acted%20without%20adhering%20to%20the%20principle%20of%20due%20process%2C%20reminds%20one%20of%20a%20lawless%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20where%20'might%20was%20right'%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20such%20%26quot%3Bhigh-handed%20and%20arbitrary%20actions%26quot%3B%20have%20no%20place%20in%20our%20Constitution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20its%20powers%20under%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20laid%20down%20guidelines%20for%20demolitions.%20It%20said%20no%20demolition%20should%20be%20carried%20out%20without%20a%20showcause%20notice.%20The%20person%20this%20notice%20is%20served%20to%20can%20respond%20within%2015%20days%20or%20the%20time%20provided%20in%20local%20civic%20laws%2C%20whichever%20is%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20notice%20must%20have%20information%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20unauthorised%20construction%2C%20details%20on%20the%20specific%20violation%20and%20the%20grounds%20for%20demolition%2C%20the%20court%20said.%20The%20authority%20concerned%20must%20hear%20the%20accused%20and%20then%20pass%20a%20final%20order%2C%20it%20added.%20The%20house%20owner%20will%20be%20given%20a%2015-day%20period%20to%20remove%20the%20illegal%20structure%20and%20authorities%20will%20proceed%20with%20a%20demolition%20only%20if%20an%20appellate%20authority%20doesn't%20pause%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViolation%20of%20the%20court's%20directions%20would%20lead%20to%20contempt%20proceedings%2C%20the%20bench%20warned.%20Officers%20should%20be%20told%20that%20if%20a%20demolition%20exercise%20is%20found%20to%20be%20in%20violation%20of%20norms%2C%20they%20will%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20restitution%20of%20the%20demolished%20property%2C%20the%20court%20said.%20The%20cost%20for%20this%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20would%20be%20recovered%20from%20the%20officials'%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20all%20local%20municipal%20authorities%20must%20set%20up%20a%20digital%20portal%20within%20three%20months%20that%20has%20details%20of%20showcause%20notices%20served%20and%20final%20orders%20on%20illegal%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20clarified%20that%20its%C2%A0directions%20won't%20be%20applicable%20for%20unauthorised%20structures%20in%20public%20places%20such%20as%20road%2C%20street%2C%20footpath%2C%20railway%20lines%20or%20water%20bodies%20and%20in%20cases%20where%20there%20is%20an%20order%20for%20demolition%20by%20a%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731487080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fch7ohea8_supreme-court-bulldozer-split_625x300_22_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flegal-process-shouldnt-prejudge-guilt-of-accused-supreme-court-on-bulldozer-justice-7007437%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Executive%20cannot%20replace%20the%20Judiciary%20and%20legal%20process%20should%20not%20prejudge%20the%20guilt%20of%20an%20accused%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20today%2C%20taking%20a%20tough%20stand%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20'bulldozer%20justice'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jeff%20Bezos'%20Ex-Wife%20Mackenzie%20Scott%20Slashes%20Amazon%20Stake%20By%20Another%20%248%20Billion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMacKenzie%20Scott%2C%20billionaire%20philanthropist%20and%20ex-wife%20of%20Amazon%20founder%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20has%20further%20cut%20down%20her%20Amazon%20stake.%20A%20November%208%20filing%20revealed%20that%20Scott%20sold%2011%20per%20cent%20of%20her%20Amazon%20shares%20valued%20at%20over%20%248%20billion%20on%20September%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20transaction%20brings%20her%20total%20Amazon%20share%20sales%20and%20gifts%20to%20255%20million%20shares%2C%20amounting%20to%20around%20%2437%20billion%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20disposals.%20With%20this%2C%20Scott%2C%20who%20received%20around%20400%20million%20Amazon%20shares%20as%20part%20of%20her%20divorce%20settlement%20with%20Bezos%20in%202019%2C%20has%20sold%20or%20donated%20two-thirds%20of%20those%20holdings%20in%20less%20than%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20makes%20her%20one%20of%20the%20five%20most%20generous%20living%20donors%20in%20the%20US%2C%20with%20at%20least%20%2417.3%20billion%20donated%20to%20non-profit%20organisations%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fphoebeliu%2F2024%2F11%2F11%2Fbillionaire-philanthropist-mackenzie-scott-sold-donated-more-amazon-shares%2F%5C%22%3EForbes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20Forbes%20estimates%20Scott's%20net%20worth%20at%20%2430%20billion%2C%20a%20drop%20from%20%2438%20billion%20just%20a%20week%20ago%2C%20and%20significantly%20down%20from%20her%20peak%20of%20%2459%20billion%20in%202021.%20Had%20she%20not%20given%20away%20her%20Amazon%20shares%2C%20her%20wealth%20would%20have%20been%20closer%20to%20%2482%20billion%2C%20placing%20her%20among%20the%20top%2020%20richest%20people%20globally%20and%20making%20her%20the%20second%20richest%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Scott%20has%20never%20publicly%20discussed%20her%20philanthropic%20efforts%20in%20great%20detail%2C%20she%20regularly%20updates%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyieldgiving.com%2Fessays%2Fbridges-and-barriers%5C%22%3EYield%20Giving%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lists%20grants%20made%20to%20various%20causes.%20In%20one%20of%20her%20essays%20in%20December%202022%2C%20Scott%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CInformation%20from%20other%20people%20%E2%80%93%20other%20givers%2C%20my%20team%2C%20the%20non-profit%20teams%20I've%20been%20giving%20to%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20enormously%20helpful%20to%20me.%E2%80%9D%20She%20also%20reflected%20on%20the%20challenges%20of%20creating%20a%20platform%20that%20properly%20conveys%20her%20philanthropic%20intentions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScott%20has%20recently%20given%20%241.5%20million%20to%20the%20Mni%20Sota%20Fund%2C%20a%20non-profit%20organisation%20that%20builds%20wealth%20for%20urban%20Native%20people%20in%20Minnesota.%20Then%20Access%20to%20Capital%20for%20Entrepreneurs%20in%20Georgia%20received%20%2410%20million%20in%20August%20from%20her.%20Additionally%2C%20Coastal%20Enterprises%2C%20an%20organisation%20focused%20on%20rural%20economic%20development%20in%20Maine%2C%20was%20given%20%2415%20million%20in%20October%202024%2C%20marking%20a%20rare%20second%20donation%20to%20the%20same%20organisation%20from%20Scott%2C%20according%20to%20Forbes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScott%20often%20opts%20not%20to%20publicise%20her%20donations%20unless%20requested%20by%20the%20recipients.%20Each%20year%2C%20Scott%20unveils%20new%20grants%20through%20her%20Yield%20Giving%20platform%2C%20usually%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20calendar%20year.%20It's%20likely%20that%20some%20of%20the%20Amazon%20shares%20sold%20in%20this%20recent%20filing%20were%20directed%20to%20non-profit%20groups%20as%20part%20of%20her%20ongoing%20charitable%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20%2437%20billion%20in%20Amazon%20shares%20Scott%20has%20offloaded%20so%20far%2C%20she%20has%20announced%20donations%20of%20%2417.3%20billion%20to%20more%20than%202%2C300%20organisations.%20The%20remaining%20value%20from%20the%20sales%20is%20likely%20held%20in%20donor-advised%20funds%20or%20other%20charitable%20accounts%2C%20with%20some%20funds%20possibly%20already%20being%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScott's%20unique%20approach%20to%20philanthropy%20has%20garnered%20attention%20for%20its%20simplicity%20and%20effectiveness.%20She%20does%20not%20actively%20solicit%20requests%20for%20grants%2C%20except%20for%20her%20Open%20Call%20initiative%2C%20which%20awarded%20%24640%20million%20to%20361%20organisations%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Her%20unrestricted%20cash%20grants%2C%20which%20are%20often%20larger%20than%20an%20organisation's%20annual%20budget%2C%20have%20made%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20many%20smaller%20charities.%20For%20instance%2C%20Dianne%20Calvi%2C%20CEO%20of%20Village%20Enterprises%2C%20a%20non-profit%20tackling%20poverty%20in%20rural%20Africa%2C%20noted%20that%20Scott's%20%247%20million%20donation%20last%20year%20significantly%20boosted%20the%20organisation's%20reputation%2C%20leading%20to%20additional%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731486660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fu42n69_mackenzie-scott_625x300_13_November_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmackenzie-scott-s-net-worth-drops-to-30-billion-after-latest-amazon-share-sale-7008222%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22MacKenzie%20Scott%2C%20the%20ex-wife%20of%20Amazon%20founder%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20received%20around%20400%20million%20Amazon%20shares%20as%20part%20of%20her%20divorce%20settlement%20in%202019.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Champions%20Trophy%20Row%20Escalates%2C%20Report%20Says%20Pak%20Government%20Asked%20PCB%20To...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20impasse%20over%20the%20ICC%20Champions%20Trophy's%20model%20continues%20after%20the%20Pakistan%20government%20has%20reportedly%20asked%20the%20board%20not%20to%20shift%20any%20game%20outside%20the%20country.%20The%20Board%20of%20Control%20for%20Cricket%20in%20India%20(BCCI)%20recently%20informed%20the%20International%20Cricket%20Council%20(ICC)%20of%20the%20Indian%20government's%20decision%20to%20not%20send%20its%20team%20across%20the%20border.%20However%2C%20Pakistan%20also%20remained%20determined%20to%20not%20let%20a%20single%20match%20go%20outside%20the%20country%2C%20having%20won%20the%20rights%20to%20organise%20the%20entire%20tournament%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PCB%20had%20sought%20assistance%20from%20the%20Pakistan%20government%20on%20the%20matter.%20A%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fpakistan-unwilling-champions-trophy-2025-hybrid-india-refusal-9666956%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20now%20claimed%20that%20the%20Pakistan%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20allow%20a%20single%20game%20to%20be%20taken%20outside%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20told%20by%20our%20government%20not%20to%20move%20any%20game%20out%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20that%20will%20be%20our%20stand%20when%20the%20time%20comes.%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20ICC%20has%20just%20informed%20us%20about%20India's%20decision.%20We%20have%20the%20hosting%20rights%20for%20the%20Champions%20Trophy%20so%20there%20is%20no%20way%20we%20can%20move%20the%20games%20outside%20Pakistan%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20PCB%20official%20told%20the%20paper%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Pakistan%20cricketer%20Basit%20Ali%20also%20confirmed%20the%20same%20during%20a%20video%20on%20his%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20saying%20the%20country's%20government%20has%20barred%20PCB%20from%20accepting%20the%20hybrid%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Pakistan%20keen%20on%20hosting%20the%20entire%20event%20at%20home%20and%20India%20not%20willing%20to%20cross%20the%20border%20over%20security%20concerns%2C%20the%20Champions%20Trophy%20sees%20its%20fate%20hanging%20in%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20had%20earlier%20claimed%20that%20the%20tournament%20could%20also%20be%20shifted%20to%20South%20Africa%20if%20no%20common%20ground%20is%20achieved%20by%20the%20PCB%20and%20BCCI.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20Pakistan%20is%20unlikely%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20suggestions%20also%20indicate%20that%20the%20tournament%20could%20be%20held%20without%20either%20of%20the%20two%20teams%2C%20but%20such%20a%20compromise%20would%20have%20a%20huge%20financial%20impact%20on%20ICC%20and%20its%20revenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20vs%20Pakistan%20cricket%20games%20don't%20just%20drive%20money%20for%20the%20two%20teams'%20boards%20but%20also%20give%20ICC%2C%20and%20in%20the%20process%20other%20teams%2C%20a%20healthy%20revenue-generating%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17314