2C%20with%20development%20starting%20in%202002%20and%20its%20first%20commercial%20flight%20taking%20off%20in%20June%202016.%20Its%20previous%20name%2C%20the%20ARJ21%2C%20stood%20for%20Advanced%20Regional%20Jet%20for%20the%2021st%20Century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225397%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20staff%20member%20standing%20inside%20a%20C909%20plane%20with%20empty%20seats.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734339c5ec9bfa3d63db882%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20C909%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20the%20ARJ21%2C%20is%20a%20smaller%20plane%20that%20seats%20five%20abreast.%3Cp%3EChen%20Duo%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20regional%20plane%2C%20it's%20technically%20fit%20for%20flights%20up%20to%20four%20or%20five%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20think%20trips%20such%20as%20New%20York%20City%20to%20Miami.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20Boeing%20and%20Airbus%20duopoly%20should%20have%20little%20to%20fear%20from%20the%20Chinese%20plane.%20Offering%20about%2070%20to%2090%20seats%2C%20the%20C909%20is%20often%20compared%20to%20the%20Boeing%20717%2C%20which%20was%20marketed%20to%20airlines%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfc0c2c2-79a5-4f1f-98b7-ec49ac166432%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20C909%20fits%20into%20COMAC's%20plans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Yu%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20New%20York%20University%20Shanghai%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20rebrand%20displayed%20COMAC's%20intention%20to%20go%20international%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20market%20norms%2C%20really%20no%20other%20player%20has%20done%20this%20in%20terms%20of%20rebranding%20their%20aircraft.%20Unless%20it's%20in%20an%20M%26amp%3BA%20play%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yu%2C%20who%20also%20runs%20the%20advisory%20firm%20Asia%20Aviation%20Valuation%20Advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOMAC%20is%20expected%20to%20soon%20debut%20another%20plane%20with%20a%20similar%20name%2C%20the%20C929%2C%20a%20larger%20290-passenger%20aircraft.%20The%20Chinese%20firm%20is%20also%20working%20on%20an%20even%20bigger%20plane%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Feconomy%2Fchina-economy%2Farticle%2F3262476%2Fchina-begins-work-new-c939-widebody-jet-going-bigger-and-bolder-after-c919s-success%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EC939%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20wide-body%20jet%20with%20390%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20said%20renaming%20the%20ARJ21%20as%20the%20C909%20would%20allow%20the%20Chinese%20planemaker%20to%20market%20a%20full%20range%20of%20aircraft%20variants%20under%20one%20name%20%E2%80%94%20just%20like%20how%20Airbus%20and%20Boeing%20sell%20their%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%2C%20for%20example%2C%20provides%20a%20range%20of%20seat%20capacities%20from%20138%20to%20204%20passengers%20through%20the%20737%20Max%207%2C%208%2C%209%2C%20and%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20change%20the%20plane's%20technical%20capabilities%2C%20but%20it%20streamlines%20the%20company's%20offerings%20into%20one%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20it%20from%20a%20holistic%20perspective%2C%20they%20want%20the%20smallest%20aircraft%20and%20the%20biggest%20aircraft%2C%20and%20every%20single%20segment%20in%20between%20to%20be%20competitive%2C%26quot%3B%20Yu%20said%20of%20COMAC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3276065-bc04-4348-9885-f6c2ecc6c357%5C%22%3EA%20new%20name%20doesn't%20mean%20more%20sales%20for%20the%20C909%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20its%20Tuesday%20announcement%20at%20the%20Zhuhai%20air%20show%20in%20China%2C%20COMAC%20said%20the%20C909%20would%20be%20lighter%2C%20more%20resistant%2C%20and%20less%20noisy%20than%20the%20ARJ21.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Brendan%20Sobie%2C%20an%20aviation%20consultant%20in%20Singapore%2C%20said%20the%20new%20name%20might%20not%20help%20COMAC%20sell%20the%20C909%20internationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20the%20plane's%20aged%20tech%20puts%20it%20at%20a%20disadvantage%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20you%20have%20a%20new%20aircraft%2C%20it's%20about%20when%20the%20plane%20was%20initially%20developed.%20With%20this%2C%20everything%20was%20selected%2020%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Sobie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20over%20100%20of%20the%20Chinese%20aircraft%20have%20been%20sold%20to%20Chinese%20airlines%20and%20TransNusa%20Airlines%2C%20an%20Indonesian%20carrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESobie%20added%20that%20more%20attention%20had%20instead%20been%20focused%20on%20the%20milestone%20narrow-body%20C919.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20interior%20of%20a%20COMAC%20C919%2C%20seen%20from%20the%20Business%20Class%20cabin%20area.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673434415ec9bfa3d63db888%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECOMAC's%20larger%20and%20newer%20C919%20typically%20sits%20six%20abreast%20and%20is%20meant%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20the%20737%20and%20A320.%3Cp%3EPETER%20PARKS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newer%20plane's%20launch%20has%20come%20as%20both%20Airbus%20and%20Boeing%20suffer%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Fairbus-boeing-aircraft-delivery-delays-not-improving-iata-head-says-2024-10-16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivery%20delays%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20frustrated%20their%20airline%20customers.%20Over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Boeing%20has%20also%20faced%20a%20reckoning%20over%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-safety-mess-just-got-worse-2024-10%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520National%2520Transportation%2520Safety%2520Board%2Cbeen%2520plagued%2520by%2520safety%2520probes.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20safety%20of%20its%20737s%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-boeing-737-max-9-door-blowout-company-response-earnings-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoor%20plug%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0blew%20out%20of%20one%20of%20its%20planes%20mid-flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20some%20kind%20of%20appetite%20for%20another%20player%20in%20the%20market%2C%20but%20COMAC%20has%20to%20overcome%20a%20lot%20of%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20Sobie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20neither%20the%20C919%20nor%20the%20C909%20are%20certified%20by%20American%20or%20European%20aviation%20authorities%2C%20though%20COMAC%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Fold-friend-new-look-chinas-comac-renames-regional-jet-c909-marketing-push-2024-11-12%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushing%20hard%20for%20the%20C919's%20approval%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20haven't%20seen%20a%20big%2C%20flagship%2C%20independently%20managed%20airline%20commit%20yet%20to%20these%20aircraft%20because%20they%20do%20have%20to%20be%20certified%2C%26quot%3B%20Sobie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20the%20manufacturer%20and%20its%20C909%20could%20pose%20a%20greater%20threat%20to%20Boeing%20and%20Airbus%20is%20China.%20Domestic%20airlines%20there%20operate%20more%20than%204%2C300%20Boeing%20planes%20and%201%2C700%20Airbus%20aircraft%2C%20and%20China%20has%20already%20approved%20COMAC's%20planes%20for%20commercial%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaltimes.cn%2Fpage%2F202411%2F1322907.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20lauded%20the%20C909%20rebrand%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20reporting%20that%20local%20airlines%20had%20ordered%2070%20of%20the%20renamed%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20said%20that%20if%20COMAC%20could%20make%20the%20C919%20and%20C909%20economically%20attractive%20to%20airlines%2C%20it%20stood%20a%20chance%20of%20grabbing%20market%20share%20both%20at%20home%20and%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%2C%20ultimately%2C%20the%20question%20is%20whether%20the%20airline%20can%20make%20money%20off%20of%20it.%20That's%20the%20main%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Airbus%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20COMAC's%20developments%20would%20%26quot%3Bnot%20stop%20us%20from%20being%20present%20in%20the%20markets%20where%20we%20have%20significant%20customer%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20always%20indicated%20that%20we%20saw%20upcoming%20competition%20from%20COMAC%2C%20and%20it%20is%20now%20a%20reality%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20Chinese%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-renaming-regional-jet-c909-arj21-boeing-airbus-comac-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731482146000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673438ea88cea3ba1c2050eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-renaming-regional-jet-c909-arj21-boeing-airbus-comac-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ARJ21%20is%20now%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20C909.%20The%20renaming%20plays%20into%20COMAC's%20ambition%20to%20enter%20the%20global%20market.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A153%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-renaming-regional-jet-c909-arj21-boeing-airbus-comac-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vicky%20drops%20powerful%20FIRST%20LOOK%20for%20%E2%80%98Mahavatar%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731481507000%2C%22v