3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F115242870.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EMusician%20Brooks%20Young%2C%2042%2C%20known%20for%20his%20collaborations%20with%20renowned%20artists%20like%20B.B.%20King%20and%20Bryan%20Adams%2C%20passed%20away%20in%20a%20car%20accident%20in%20New%20Hampshire.%20Young%2C%20who%20was%20on%20a%20nationwide%20tour%2C%20was%20scheduled%20to%20perform%20his%20final%20show%20later%20this%20year.%20Family%20and%20fellow%20musicians%20expressed%20their%20grief%2C%20remembering%20Young's%20talent%20and%20kind%20nature.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Nurse%20Shares%20What%20Happens%20Moments%20After%20A%20Person%20Dies%3A%20%26quot%3BBody%20Relaxes...%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJulie%20McFadden%2C%20a%20seasoned%20nurse%20in%20the%20US%20with%20extensive%20experience%20in%20intensive%20care%2C%20has%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20bodily%20changes%20that%20occur%20after%20death.%20Having%20witnessed%20numerous%20deaths%20throughout%20her%20career%2C%20Ms%20McFadden%20aims%20to%20remove%20the%20stigma%20and%20fear%20surrounding%20death.%20After%20transitioning%20to%20hospice%20care%2C%20she%20started%20a%20YouTube%20channel%20that%20offers%20candid%20answers%20to%20common%20questions%20about%20dying.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DehwNkIQ_T2w%5C%22%3Eviral%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20garnering%20over%20590%2C000%20views%2C%20explains%20exactly%20what%20happens%20to%20the%20human%20body%20after%20death%2C%20to%20try%20and%20demystify%20the%20experience.%20In%20the%20video%2C%20she%20outlined%20the%20physical%20changes%20that%20occur%20in%20the%20body%20after%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20body%20'relaxes'%20after%20death%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nurse%20explained%20that%20the%20body%20undergoes%20a%20natural%20relaxation%20process%20right%20after%20death%2C%20which%20she%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bmessy.%26quot%3B%C2%A0This%20is%20the%20first%20stage%20of%20decomposition%2C%20called%20hypostasis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20to%20your%20body%20immediately%20after%20it%20dies%3F%20It%20relaxes%2C%20just%20like%20I've%20been%20saying.%20This%20is%20why%20some%20people%20might%20urinate%2C%20have%20bowel%20movements%2C%20or%20even%20experience%20fluids%20coming%20from%20their%20nose%2C%20eyes%2C%20or%20ears.%20Essentially%2C%20all%20the%20muscles%20and%20systems%20that%20typically%20contain%20bodily%20fluids%20relax.%20That's%20why%20death%20can%20get%20a%20little%20messy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBody%20temperature%20drops%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Nurse%20Julie%2C%20every%20individual's%20body%20reacts%20differently%20after%20death.%20The%20cooling%20process%2C%20known%20as%20algor%20mortis%2C%20can%20begin%20immediately%20for%20some%2C%20while%20others%20may%20experience%20a%20delay%20of%20up%20to%20one%20or%20two%20hours.%20On%20average%2C%20body%20temperature%20drops%20by%201.5%20degrees%20per%20hour%20until%20it%20eventually%20reaches%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20surrounding%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Some%20people%20take%20a%20while%2C%20maybe%20an%20hour%2C%20perhaps%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half.%20It%20just%20depends%2C%20but%20their%20body%20temperature%20will%20drop.%20Technically%20speaking%2C%20the%20body%20temperature%20should%20drop%20about%20one%20and%20a%20half%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20per%20hour%20to%20eventually%20match%20whatever%20the%20temperature%20is%20in%20the%20room%20that%20they're%20in%2C''%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBlood%20pools%20downwards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Nurse%20Julie%2C%20there's%20a%20lesser-known%20phenomenon%20that%20occurs%20after%20death%2C%20which%20many%20people%20are%20unaware%20of.%20When%20someone%20dies%2C%20the%20blood%20in%20their%20body%20begins%20to%20move%20towards%20the%20ground%20due%20to%20gravity%2C%20a%20process%20known%20as%20livor%20mortis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3EShe%20said%2C%20''If%20you%20let%20someone%20lie%20there%20for%20long%20enough%20-%20which%20we%20do%20sometimes%3B%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20hurry%20up%20and%20make%20sure%20your%20loved%20one%20leaves%20the%20house%20-%20if%20you%20turn%20them%20you%20will%20notice%20usually%20the%20back%20of%20their%20legs%20the%20whole%20backside%20of%20them%20will%20look%20purple%20or%20darker%20that's%20because%20all%20their%20blood%20is%20pulling%20down.%20Gravity%20is%20pulling%20it%20down.%20So%20they%20will%20eventually%20get%20a%20darker%20colour%20tone%20of%20skin%20on%20their%20backside.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20body%20stiffens%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3ENext%20is%20the%20stiffening%20of%20the%20muscles%20due%20to%20the%20halting%20of%20metabolic%20processes.%20Rigor%20mortis%20typically%20begins%20within%202-4%20hours%20post-mortem%20and%20can%20last%20for%20up%20to%2072%20hours%2C%20depending%20on%20factors%20such%20as%20environmental%20conditions%20and%20individual%20physical%20characteristics.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20the%20body%20becomes%20''very%20very%20heavy''%20after%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI've%20witnessed%20individuals%20become%20rigid%20mere%20minutes%20after%20passing%2C%20while%20others%20take%20longer%20to%20exhibit%20this%20stiffness%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-t%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bn%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BblueLinks%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20body%20will%20feel%20cool%20to%20the%20touch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%2012%20hours%20post-mortem%2C%20the%20body's%20temperature%20regulation%20stops%2C%20making%20it%20feel%20cool%20to%20the%20touch.%20ATP%2C%20the%20vital%20energy%20currency%2C%20is%20no%20longer%20generated%2C%20causing%20the%20body's%20temperature%20to%20drop.%20The%20nurse%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20happens%20because%20your%20body's%20metabolism%20stops%20and%20it%20can%20no%20longer%20produce%20ATP%2C%20which%20is%20adenosine%20triphosphate%2C%20which%20is%20a%20mouthful%20for%20me%20to%20say%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20body's%20cellular%20energy.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20putrefaction%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20phase%20of%20the%20body's%20decomposition%20process%20is%20known%20as%20putrefaction%20or%20purification.%20%26quot%3BThis%20stage%20is%20where%20the%20body%20breaks%20down%2C%20returning%20to%20its%20natural%20state.%20It's%20how%20bodies%20would%20decompose%20naturally%2C%20before%20the%20existence%20of%20mortuaries%20and%20modern%20funeral%20practices%2C''%20she%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20putrefaction%20is%20a%20normal%20part%20of%20the%20decomposition%20process%2C%20Nurse%20Julie%20acknowledged%20that%20it's%20rarely%20witnessed.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20usually%20aren't%20exposed%20to%20it...%20but%20this%20is%20a%20natural%20part%20of%20the%20body%20decomposing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731477300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fef6jgtno_human-body_625x300_13_November_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fus-nurse-shares-reality-of-what-happens-moments-after-a-person-dies-the-body-relaxes-7007528%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Her%20YouTube%20video%20explains%20exactly%20wha