20lead%20to%20reduced%20soil%20moisture.%20While%20cool%20weather%20reduces%20evaporation%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20rainfall%20can%20still%20dry%20out%20soils%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20crops%20to%20access%20water.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20black%20or%20clayey%20soil%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20retain%20moisture%2C%20softer%20soils%20don%E2%80%99t%2C%20so%20farmers%20should%20understand%20their%20soil%20type%20and%20plan%20accordingly%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Savita.%20Farmers%20can%20use%20mulches%20to%20help%20retain%20moisture%20and%20apply%20water%20conservation%20techniques%20like%20drip%20irrigation%20or%20rainwater%20harvesting%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20soil%20moisture.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Manage%20soil%20pH%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECold%20temperatures%20and%20winter%20rains%20can%20increase%20soil%20acidity%20in%20high-rainfall%20areas%20like%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20(in%20Kerala%20and%20Karnataka)%20and%20the%20Northeast%20(in%20Assam).%20Increased%20acidity%20can%20affect%20nutrient%20retention%2C%20making%20it%20more%20challenging%20to%20grow%20crops%20like%20rice%2C%20soybean%2C%20and%20cotton.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20neutralise%20acidity%2C%20farmers%20should%20test%20soil%20pH%20regularly%20and%20apply%20lime%20or%20dolomite%20to%20restore%20a%20more%20neutral%20environment%20suitable%20for%20a%20range%20of%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E7.%20Control%20erosion%20with%20terracing%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeavy%20rains%20in%20winter%2C%20particularly%20in%20hilly%20regions%20like%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20Sikkim%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20Uttarakhand%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20increased%20soil%20erosion%2C%20washing%20away%20valuable%20topsoil.%20This%20can%20negatively%20affect%20crops%20such%20as%20tea%2C%20coffee%2C%20and%20rice%2C%20which%20