%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDocumenting%20changing%20food%20habits%20across%20geographies%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20a%20nondescript%20food%20stall%20in%20Ladakh%20where%20JNU%20(Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi)%20PhD%20scholar%2C%20Fida%20Husain%E2%80%99s%20aunt%20Ama%20Haji%20would%20get%20her%20fill%20of%20%3Cem%3EYarkhandi%20pulao%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20her%20essay%2C%20Fida%20writes%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3EYarkandi%20polla%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereflects%20the%20cultural%20heritage%20of%20Ladakh%20as%20a%20confluence%20of%20cultures.%20%E2%80%9CMade%20the%20traditional%20way%20%E2%80%94%20slow-cooked%20in%20a%20heavy%20stone%20pot%20called%20a%20%3Cem%3Edoltok%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20%3Cem%3ELadakhi%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20dish%20was%20said%20to%20be%20symbolic%20of%20the%20big%20hearts%20(read%3A%20deep%20pockets)%20of%20the%20hosts%20for%20their%20guests.%20This%20bounty%20was%20proven%20by%20the%20amount%20of%20fat%2Fghee%20dripping%20down%20one%E2%80%99s%20elbows%20while%20eating.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFun%20fact%3A%20Ladakh%20was%20a%20stranger%20to%20rice%2C%20the%20protagonist%20of%20the%20dish%2C%20until%20about%20seven%20decades%20ago.%20It%20was%20improved%20transport%20links%20and%20connectivity%20that%20transformed%20the%20once%20luxury%20item%20into%20a%20staple%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F282445%2Findia-in-pics-ten-local-ladakhi-dish-history-culture-kunzes-angmo-instagram%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Ladakhi%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%203147px)%20100vw%2C%203147px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%223147%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tarana%20Husain%20Khan%20interacted%20with%20a%20number%20of%20culinary%20virtuosos%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20behind%20South%20Asian%20cuisine%20and%20its%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20current%20gastronomic%20landscape%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982.jpg%203147w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-300x288.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-500x480.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-768x737.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-1536x1474.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-2048x1965.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-1200x1151.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-150x144.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374455%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223019%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETarana%20Husain%20Khan%20interacted%20with%20many%20culinary%20virtuosos%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20behind%20South%20Asian%20cuisine%20and%20its%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20current%20gastronomic%20landscape%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20Northeast%2C%20local%20sensibilities%20dictated%20recipes%2C%20in%20Central%20and%20Eastern%20India%2C%20it%20was%20royal%20customs%20that%20did.%20This%20is%20what%20Tarana%20discovered%20during%20her%20stay%20at%20Bhopal%E2%80%99s%20Jehan%20Numa%20Palace%20Hotel%20%E2%80%94%20which%20belongs%20to%20the%20descendants%20of%20Nawab%20Sultan%20Jahan%20Begum%E2%80%99s%20second%20son%2C%20Nawab%20Muhammad%20Obaidullah%20Khan%2C%20and%20is%20known%20for%20its%20preservation%20of%20heirloom%20recipes%20of%20Bhopal%E2%80%99s%20Nawabi%20cuisine.%20Here%2C%20she%20enjoyed%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20two%20dishes%20with%20a%20rich%20history%3A%20the%20%3Cem%3EBhopali%20rezala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(chicken%20cooked%20with%20spinach)%20%E2%80%94%20which%20she%20learnt%2C%20amalgamates%20the%20local%20flavours%20with%20%3Cem%3EAwadhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Mughal%20cuisine%20and%20is%20popular%20in%20West%20Bengal%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20unique%20mincemeat%20preparation).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20more%20about%20these%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CBhopalis%20apparently%20prepared%20%3Cem%3Erezala%20%3C%2Fem%3Efrom%20peacock%20meat%20until%20hunting%20peacocks%20was%20banned.%20As%20for%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349748%2Flaal-maas-history-recipe-best-places-to-eat-in-rajasthan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunting%20traditions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bhopal.%20Upon%20the%20killing%20of%20an%20animal%20%E2%80%93%20usually%20nilgai%2C%20deer%20or%20gazelle%20%E2%80%93%20its%20meat%20was%20coarsely%20chopped%20or%20sliced%20into%20slivers%20while%20still%20warm%2C%20and%20immediately%20fried%20with%20some%20basic%20ingredients%20on%20a%20campfire.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20made%20for%20a%20rustic%20meal%20for%20the%20hunters.%20The%20modern%20version%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%20%3C%2Fem%3Eincludes%20hand-chopped%20mincemeat%20cooked%20with%20ginger%E2%80%93garlic%20paste%2C%20turmeric%2C%20chillies%2C%20onions%2C%20yoghurt%20and%20coriander.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20book%20takes%20its%20course%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20taken%20on%20a%20winding%20journey%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%20From%20%3Cem%3Eqiwami%20seviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(whose%20recipe%20Karachi-based%20writer%20Muneeza%20Shamsie%20chanced%20upon%20after%20her%20mother%E2%80%99s%20passing)%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F266943%2Fwinter-food-map-traditional-indian-recipes-gajar-ka-halwa-nolen-gur-syku-daulat-ki-chaat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewinter%20staple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Esarson%20ka%20saag%3C%2Fem%3E%20(shared%20by%20Moneeza%20Hashmi%2C%20daughter%20of%20the%20legendary%20poet%20Faiz%20Ahmed%20Faiz)%20to%20historian%20Rana%20Safvi%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Elahsan%20mirch%20ki%20chutney%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20digital%20archivist%20Farah%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Ekaleji%20fry%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eamidst%20others%20%E2%80%94%20each%20chapter%20conjures%20an%20image%20of%20the%20pomp%20and%20splendour%20the%20dish%20enjoyed%20in%20its%20heyday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20recipe%2C%20the%20hope%20is%20that%20these%20dishes%20may%20once%20more%20find%20a%20way%20back%20into%20our%20kitchens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730815914000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fshami-kebabs-1730811763.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D374418%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr%20Tarana%20Husain%20Khan%20was%20part%20of%20the%20team%20that%20compiled%20essays%20by%20food%20writers%20across%20South%20Asia%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20highlight%20the%20'Forgotten%20Foods'%20of%20India%20and%20how%20they%20shaped%20present-day%20culinary%20practices.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F374418%2Ftarana-husain-khan-book-forgotten-foods-south-asian-food-history-kababs-qormas-rampur-food-writers%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boeing%20Strike%20Ends%20After%2053%20Days%20As%20Workers%20Accept%20Contract%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20deal%20includes%20a%2038%25%20raise%20for%20employees%20over%20four%20years%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20high